FIXES #23 (CHECK FOR ACTIVE?INACTIVE STATUS OF 2 STEP VERIFICATION)
The way this commit works is it places a code under try block to check whether 2 step verification is active. If yes then it exits the program without any error and with a message to the user to deactivate 2 step verification before running the code. If 2 step verification id not active then it raises an exception which means we are good to go and thus the exception is passed,then finally block is executed to do the task the code is intended to do.

->This modification gives  the user and option for the type of output file.  For PDF input is 1 and for .txt input is 2.
->The ' encode('latin-1', 'ignore') ' code eliminates any character which is not included in the ASCII code. This is essential for writing the
    text in .pdf format.  Next the ' decode('latin-1') ' part again decodes the rectified string into byte-form as the FPDF.cel() command
